# GitNexus ignore patterns — controls which files are indexed for code intelligence.
# Syntax matches .gitignore. Use `!pattern` to override a default ignore.

# Skip the docs/ tree. PRDs, design specs, and game-system documentation
# inflate the graph with thousands of `Section` nodes (markdown headings)
# without adding code intelligence value. Architecture references stay
# discoverable via the filesystem; we just don't want them as graph symbols.
docs/

# Skip top-level design/process docs that aren't code intelligence material.
# AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md are GitNexus-managed (auto-rewritten by `analyze`)
# so indexing them creates a circular reference and adds no signal.
README.md
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
BACKLOG.md
CHANGELOG.md

# Skip asset-folder workflow READMEs (image generation guides, asset naming
# conventions). They show up as large `Section` clusters under "Components"
# / "Assets" but represent no executable code.
**/assets/**/README.md
**/assets/**/*.md
app/frontend/public/assets/**/*.md

# Skip test-only documentation (migration verification notes, manual test
# scripts written as markdown).
app/backend/tests/**/*.md
app/frontend/tests/**/*.md

# Skip cycle log dumps generated at runtime.
app/backend/cycle_logs/

# Skip Kiro/Claude tooling metadata. Steering files are workflow config, not
# code, and indexing them creates noise communities.
.kiro/
.claude/
